cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.CY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on enhancing user experience for multi-screen social TV streaming over wireless networks. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a likely category as the paper discusses video quality of experience (QoE) and resource efficiency in social TV streaming. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the paper explores the social aspects of multi-screen cloud social TV. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a potential category as the paper discusses the user experience of social TV and proposes a framework to enhance it. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the social implications of multi-screen cloud social TV.
